{%- comment -%}
  Component: mallem-product-card
  Purpose: Premium reusable product card for collections, search, recommendations
  Used in: Collection grids, featured products, search results, related products

  Features:
  - Add to cart button with AJAX support
  - Responsive images with hover effect
  - Badge system (sale, sold out, custom metafields, featured)
  - Price display with discount calculation
  - Quick view and wishlist buttons
  - Variant swatches (color/label) with live image + ATC button sync
  - RTL-ready with CSS logical properties
  - Mobile-first design optimized for MENA markets

  Parameters:
  - product {Object} Required - Shopify product object
  - show_vendor {Boolean} Optional - Display product vendor (default: false)
  - show_quick_view {Boolean} Optional - Show quick view button (default: settings.mallem_enable_quick_view)
  - show_wishlist {Boolean} Optional - Show wishlist button (default: settings.mallem_enable_wishlist)
  - image_ratio {String} Optional - Image aspect ratio: square, portrait, landscape (default: settings.mallem_product_image_ratio)
  - lazy_load {Boolean} Optional - Enable lazy loading (default: true)
  - show_badges {Boolean} Optional - Display product badges (default: true)
  - enable_hover_image {Boolean} Optional - Show second image on hover (default: true)
  - show_swatches {Boolean} Optional - Display variant swatches below title (default: true)
  - swatch_option {String} Optional - Which option to render swatches for (default: first option)

  RTL: Fully RTL-compatible via CSS logical properties
  Performance: Lazy loading, explicit dimensions, lightweight animations, deferred JS
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- liquid
  comment
    WHY defaults: Provide sensible fallbacks while allowing merchant control
    Settings integration allows global configuration with per-instance override
  endcomment
  assign show_vendor = show_vendor | default: false
  assign show_quick_view = show_quick_view | default: settings.mallem_enable_quick_view, allow_false: true
  assign show_wishlist = show_wishlist | default: settings.mallem_enable_wishlist, allow_false: true
  assign lazy_load = lazy_load | default: true, allow_false: true
  assign show_badges = show_badges | default: true, allow_false: true
  assign enable_hover_image = enable_hover_image | default: true, allow_false: true
  assign image_ratio = image_ratio | default: settings.mallem_product_image_ratio | default: 'square'
  assign show_swatches = show_swatches | default: true, allow_false: true
  assign swatch_option = swatch_option | default: ''

  comment
    WHY featured media: Primary product image for card display
    Fallback to placeholder prevents broken layouts when merchant hasn't uploaded images
  endcomment
  assign featured_media = product.featured_media

  comment
    WHY second image: Premium UX pattern - reveals alternate view on hover
    Desktop-only feature reduces bandwidth on mobile (critical for 3G MENA markets)
    Shows product detail without forcing navigation - improves product discovery
  endcomment
  assign second_image = null
  if enable_hover_image and product.media.size > 1
    assign second_image = product.media[1]
  endif

  comment
    WHY availability check: Core product state that controls UI rendering
    Determines badge display, button state, and messaging to user
  endcomment
  assign is_sold_out = false
  if product.available == false
    assign is_sold_out = true
  endif

  comment
    WHY sale detection: Discount pricing is primary conversion driver in MENA markets
    Compare-at price indicates merchant's original price before promotion
  endcomment
  assign on_sale = false
  if product.compare_at_price > product.price
    assign on_sale = true
  endif

  comment
    WHY metafield badges: Merchants need flexible badge system for marketing campaigns
    Custom badges: "New", "Hot", "Limited", "Pre-order", seasonal promotions, etc.
    Featured badge: Highlight premium products in collections
    Namespace 'mallem' keeps theme-specific data organized and conflict-free
  endcomment
  assign custom_badge = product.metafields.mallem.badge_text
  assign featured_badge = product.metafields.mallem.featured

  comment
    WHY explicit dimensions: Prevent Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS) - critical for Core Web Vitals
    Browser can reserve correct space before image loads, preventing layout jumps
    Improves perceived performance and user experience, especially on slow connections
  endcomment
  assign image_width = 600
  assign image_height = 600
  if image_ratio == 'portrait'
    assign image_height = 750
  elsif image_ratio == 'landscape'
    assign image_height = 450
  endif

  comment
    WHY first available variant: Ensures add-to-cart form has valid variant ID
    Product may have multiple variants; we need one default for the form
  endcomment
  assign first_variant = product.selected_or_first_available_variant
-%}

{%- comment -%}
  CARD WRAPPER
  WHY BEM naming: Predictable CSS targeting, prevents class name conflicts
  WHY data attributes: Provide hooks for JavaScript without coupling to classes
{%- endcomment -%}
<div
  class="mallem-product-card mallem-product-card--{{ image_ratio }}"
  data-mallem-product-card
  data-mallem-product-id="{{ product.id }}"
  data-mallem-variant-id="{{ first_variant.id }}"
>
  {%- comment -%}
    WHY link wrapper: Makes entire card clickable - standard e-commerce UX pattern
    Accessibility: Semantic link with descriptive ARIA label for screen readers
  {%- endcomment -%}
  <a
    href="{{ product.url }}"
    class="mallem-product-card__link"
    aria-label="{{ 'products.product.view_product' | t: product_title: product.title }}"
  >
    {%- comment -%}
      MEDIA CONTAINER
      WHY isolated container: Manages aspect ratio, badge positioning, hover effects
      Contains: primary image, secondary image (hover), badges, action buttons
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <div class="mallem-product-card__media mallem-product-card__media--{{ image_ratio }}">
      {%- comment -%}
        PRIMARY IMAGE
        WHY srcset: Delivers optimal image size based on screen density and viewport
        WHY sizes: Tells browser which image to download before layout is complete
        WHY loading="lazy": Defers offscreen images - critical for mobile performance on 3G
        Images load only when user scrolls near them, improves initial page load
      {%- endcomment -%}
      {%- if featured_media -%}
        <img
          src="{{ featured_media | image_url: width: image_width }}"
          srcset="
            {{ featured_media | image_url: width: 300 }} 300w,
            {{ featured_media | image_url: width: 600 }} 600w,
            {{ featured_media | image_url: width: 900 }} 900w
          "
          sizes="(min-width: 990px) 25vw, (min-width: 750px) 33vw, 50vw"
          alt="{{ featured_media.alt | escape }}"
          width="{{ image_width }}"
          height="{{ image_height }}"
          {% if lazy_load %}loading="lazy"{% endif %}
          class="mallem-product-card__image mallem-product-card__image--primary"
          data-mallem-card-image
        >

        {%- comment -%}
          SECONDARY IMAGE (HOVER)
          WHY desktop-only: Mobile hover is unreliable and wastes bandwidth
          WHY hidden by default: CSS reveals on hover, prevents double image load
          WHY always lazy: User might not hover, so defer load until needed
        {%- endcomment -%}
        {%- if second_image -%}
          <img
            src="{{ second_image | image_url: width: image_width }}"
            srcset="
              {{ second_image | image_url: width: 300 }} 300w,
              {{ second_image | image_url: width: 600 }} 600w,
              {{ second_image | image_url: width: 900 }} 900w
            "
            sizes="(min-width: 990px) 25vw, (min-width: 750px) 33vw, 50vw"
            alt="{{ second_image.alt | escape }}"
            width="{{ image_width }}"
            height="{{ image_height }}"
            loading="lazy"
            class="mallem-product-card__image mallem-product-card__image--secondary"
          >
        {%- endif -%}
      {%- else -%}
        {%- comment -%}
          WHY placeholder: Prevents broken layout for products without images
          Shopify SVG placeholder maintains aspect ratio without external HTTP request
        {%- endcomment -%}
        <div class="mallem-product-card__placeholder">
          {{ 'product-1' | placeholder_svg_tag: 'placeholder-svg' }}
        </div>
      {%- endif -%}

      {%- comment -%}
        BADGES
        WHY priority order: Sold Out > Sale > Featured > Custom
        User needs to know availability first (can't buy if sold out)
        Then promotional pricing, then special product status
        Only show one badge to prevent visual clutter and maintain focus
      {%- endcomment -%}
      {%- if show_badges -%}
        <div class="mallem-product-card__badges">
          {%- if is_sold_out -%}
            <span class="mallem-badge mallem-badge--sold-out">
              {{ 'products.badge.sold_out' | t }}
            </span>
          {%- elsif on_sale -%}
            {%- liquid
              comment
                WHY discount percentage: MENA markets respond better to percentage vs absolute amount
                Clear value proposition - "Save 30%" more compelling than price difference
              endcomment
              assign discount = product.compare_at_price | minus: product.price
              assign discount_percent = discount | times: 100.0 | divided_by: product.compare_at_price | round
            -%}
            <span class="mallem-badge mallem-badge--sale">
              {{ 'products.badge.sale' | t }} -{{ discount_percent }}%
            </span>
          {%- elsif featured_badge -%}
            {%- comment -%}
              WHY featured badge: Highlights premium/spotlight products
              Metafield allows merchant to manually curate featured products
            {%- endcomment -%}
            <span class="mallem-badge mallem-badge--featured">
              {{ 'products.badge.featured' | t }}
            </span>
          {%- elsif custom_badge -%}
            {%- comment -%}
              WHY custom badge: Maximum merchant flexibility
              Supports seasonal campaigns: "Ramadan Sale", "Summer Collection", etc.
            {%- endcomment -%}
            <span class="mallem-badge mallem-badge--custom">
              {{ custom_badge }}
            </span>
          {%- endif -%}
        </div>
      {%- endif -%}

      {%- comment -%}
        QUICK ACTIONS
        WHY hover-show on desktop: Cleaner UI, buttons revealed on user intent
        WHY always-show on mobile: Touch devices have no reliable hover state
        Large tap targets (44px minimum) ensure accessibility on mobile
      {%- endcomment -%}
      <div class="mallem-product-card__actions">
        {%- if show_quick_view -%}
          {%- comment -%}
            QUICK VIEW BUTTON
            WHY data attributes: Unobtrusive JavaScript pattern - no inline event handlers
            data-mallem-quick-view-trigger: Hook for mallem-quick-view.js module
            data-product-handle: Used to fetch product via AJAX (/products/{handle}?view=quick-view)
            WHY handle over URL: Cleaner AJAX patterns, easier to construct fetch URLs
          {%- endcomment -%}
          <button
            type="button"
            class="mallem-product-card__action mallem-product-card__action--quick-view"
            data-mallem-quick-view-trigger
            data-product-handle="{{ product.handle }}"
            data-product-id="{{ product.id }}"
            aria-label="{{ 'products.product.quick_view' | t: product_title: product.title }}"
          >
            <svg class="mallem-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
              <path d="M10 4C5 4 1.73 7.11 1 10c.73 2.89 4 6 9 6s8.27-3.11 9-6c-.73-2.89-4-6-9-6zm0 10a4 4 0 110-8 4 4 0 010 8zm0-6.5a2.5 2.5 0 100 5 2.5 2.5 0 000-5z" fill="currentColor"/>
            </svg>
          </button>
        {%- endif -%}

        {%- if show_wishlist -%}
          {%- comment -%}
            WISHLIST BUTTON
            WHY data attribute: Hook for mallem-wishlist.js module (when implemented)
            Ready for integration - follows same pattern as quick view
          {%- endcomment -%}
          <button
            type="button"
            class="mallem-product-card__action mallem-product-card__action--wishlist"
            data-mallem-wishlist-toggle
            data-product-id="{{ product.id }}"
            aria-label="{{ 'products.product.add_to_wishlist' | t: product_title: product.title }}"
          >
            <svg class="mallem-icon" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
              <path d="M10 17.5l-1.1-1c-4-3.6-6.6-6-6.6-8.9 0-2.4 1.9-4.3 4.3-4.3 1.4 0 2.7.6 3.6 1.6.9-1 2.2-1.6 3.6-1.6 2.4 0 4.3 1.9 4.3 4.3 0 2.9-2.6 5.3-6.6 8.9l-1.1 1z" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>
            </svg>
          </button>
        {%- endif -%}
      </div>
    </div>
  </a>

  {%- comment -%}
    PRODUCT INFO
    WHY outside link: Allows interactive elements (buttons, links) without nesting
    Semantic HTML: h3 for title (assuming h2 used for section headings)
  {%- endcomment -%}
  <div class="mallem-product-card__info">
    {%- if show_vendor and product.vendor != blank -%}
      <p class="mallem-product-card__vendor">
        {{ product.vendor }}
      </p>
    {%- endif -%}

    {%- comment -%}
      WHY line clamp: Long titles break grid layouts
      2 lines maximum prevents overflow while showing enough info
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <h3 class="mallem-product-card__title">
      <a href="{{ product.url }}">{{ product.title }}</a>
    </h3>

    {%- comment -%}
      VARIANT SWATCHES
      WHY after title, before price: Swatch selection can update the displayed price
      (when variant prices differ), so swatches must sit between the two for visual logic.
      WHY show_swatches guard: Cards in tight layouts (mini-cart, sidebar) can opt out.
      enable_hover_image passed through so swatch JS knows whether to preview on hover.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    {%- if show_swatches -%}
      {%- render 'mallem-swatches',
        product: product,
        option_name: swatch_option,
        enable_hover_image: enable_hover_image
      -%}
    {%- endif -%}

    {%- comment -%}
      PRICE DISPLAY
      WHY reuse snippet: Consistent price formatting across entire theme
      mallem-price handles: sale prices, compare-at, ranges, unit prices
      Centralized logic prevents bugs from duplicate code
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <div class="mallem-product-card__price">
      {% render 'mallem-price',
        product: product,
        show_discount_badge: true,
        price_class: 'mallem-product-card__price-value'
      %}
    </div>
  </div>

  {%- comment -%}
    ADD TO CART BUTTON
    WHY outside link: Prevents invalid HTML (nested interactive elements)
    WHY form: Progressive enhancement - works without JavaScript
    WHY data-mallem-product-form: Hook for mallem-product-card.js AJAX handling
  {%- endcomment -%}
  <div class="mallem-product-card__footer">
    <form
      action="{{ routes.cart_add_url }}"
      method="post"
      class="mallem-product-card__form"
      data-mallem-product-form
    >
      {%- comment -%}
        WHY hidden inputs: Standard Shopify cart form pattern
        Form works without JS - submits to cart page
        JS intercepts and converts to AJAX for better UX
      {%- endcomment -%}
      {%- comment -%}
        WHY data-mallem-variant-id on hidden input: mallem-swatches.js updates this
        input's value when the user selects a different swatch. The form then submits
        the correct variant ID to Shopify's cart API. The card wrapper div also carries
        data-mallem-variant-id for read-only use by other modules (analytics, cart drawer);
        the JS uses input[data-mallem-variant-id] to specifically target this writable field.
      {%- endcomment -%}
      <input type="hidden" name="id" value="{{ first_variant.id }}" data-mallem-variant-id>
      <input type="hidden" name="quantity" value="1">

      {%- comment -%}
        WHY disabled state: Prevents form submission errors for unavailable products
        WHY icon + text: Visual clarity - icon helps non-readers understand action
        44px min height ensures touch-friendly tap target on mobile
      {%- endcomment -%}
      <button
        type="submit"
        class="mallem-product-card__add-button"
        {% if is_sold_out %}disabled{% endif %}
        data-mallem-add-to-cart
        aria-label="{{ 'products.product.add_to_cart' | t: product_title: product.title }}"
      >
        {%- if is_sold_out -%}
          <span class="mallem-product-card__button-text">{{ 'products.product.sold_out' | t }}</span>
        {%- else -%}
          <svg class="mallem-icon mallem-product-card__button-icon" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 18 18" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
            <path d="M6 16a1 1 0 100-2 1 1 0 000 2zM14 16a1 1 0 100-2 1 1 0 000 2zM17 4H3.42L3 1.5A1 1 0 002 1H0v1h1.58l1.5 9.5A1 1 0 004 13h11v-1H4.42l-.27-1.5H15a1 1 0 00.97-.75l2-7A1 1 0 0017 2z" fill="currentColor"/>
          </svg>
          <span class="mallem-product-card__button-text">{{ 'products.product.add_to_cart' | t }}</span>
        {%- endif -%}
      </button>
    </form>
  </div>
</div>
